{
  "id": "rheem-rgph-blower",
  "brand": "Rheem",
  "model": "RGPH-07EAMER",
  "equipment_type": "furnace",
  "symptom": "Furnace fires and heats the heat exchanger, but no air comes through the vents. Blower motor hums but doesn't spin. Limit switch trips after 2\u20133 minutes, shutting down the burners. High-temp smell from the plenum.",
  "diagnosis": "Failed blower motor (PSC type). Motor winding is partially shorted \u2014 draws locked rotor amps but can't turn. Run capacitor may test good. Common after 10\u201315 years, especially in dusty environments.",
  "part_number": "51-23012-41 (Rheem 1/2 HP PSC blower motor) \u2014 universal 5.6\" diameter PSC motor also fits",
  "procedure": [
    "Kill power at the furnace disconnect switch and breaker.",
    "Remove the blower compartment door (bottom panel on RGPH).",
    "Disconnect the motor wiring harness \u2014 note the wire colors and speed tap used (typically black = high, blue = medium-high).",
    "Remove the blower assembly: two 5/16\" bolts on the blower rail. Slide the whole assembly out.",
    "Remove the motor from the blower wheel: loosen the 5/16\" set screw on the wheel hub. May need penetrating oil if corroded.",
    "Check the run capacitor with a multimeter \u2014 if it reads within \u00b16% of rated \u00b5F, motor is the failure. If cap is bad, replace both.",
    "Install the new motor onto the blower wheel. Tighten set screw. Align wheel so it doesn't rub the housing.",
    "Reconnect wiring to the same speed tap. Reinstall the blower assembly.",
    "Restore power and run a heat cycle. Verify airflow at the registers and confirm the limit switch doesn't trip.",
    "Measure amp draw on the motor \u2014 should be at or below nameplate FLA."
  ],
  "safety_notes": [
    "The heat exchanger will be extremely hot if the blower was off during a firing cycle \u2014 wait 10 minutes before reaching into the blower compartment.",
    "Blower wheels can have sharp edges \u2014 wear gloves.",
    "If the limit switch tripped multiple times, inspect the heat exchanger for cracks (soot marks, flame rollout signs) before reassembling."
  ],
  "estimated_minutes": 45,
  "tags": [
    "blower motor",
    "no airflow",
    "motor hums",
    "limit switch",
    "RGPH",
    "rheem",
    "furnace",
    "PSC motor"
  ],
